Evenly divide the graham cracker crumbs among 6 custard cups or ramekins. Press them into the bottom. Top with banana slices. In a large saucepan, mix the sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, and salt. Stir in the milk. Whisk over medium heat until the pudding comes to a boil and thickens. Cook for 1 minute longer. Remove from the heat and stir in the vanilla. Pour into the prepared custard cups. Chill.